---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 6
  Paragraph: 49
Title: The Great And Venerable Teacher
---
\"The singular man is singular in comparison to other men, but a
companion of Heaven. So it is said, the petty man of Heaven is a
gentleman among men; the gentleman among men is the petty man of
Heaven."
